# Harbor integration: SSE streaming battery.
#
# OpenAI-compatible chat-completion streams are the highest-bandwidth path
# any proxy in front of Harbor has to handle correctly: chunked transfer,
# `data: {…}\n\n` framing, and the terminal `data: [DONE]\n\n` sentinel.
# A regression here breaks every streaming UI downstream silently.
#
# Assertions are deliberately string-shape (body contains) rather than
# parsedBody — the response is an event stream, not a single JSON object,
# so JSON path queries have nothing to walk.

@mock_openai_port = 29350
@base_url = http://localhost:{{mock_openai_port}}
@mock_model = mock-model

### Streaming chat completion ends with [DONE] and includes content deltas
# @name streaming-chat
POST {{base_url}}/v1/chat/completions
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: text/event-stream

{
  "model": "{{mock_model}}",
  "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello"}],
  "stream": true
}

?? status == 200
?? header content-type == text/event-stream
?? body contains data:
?? body contains [DONE]
?? body contains "delta"
?? body contains "content"
?? body contains "finish_reason": "stop"

###
